a:260:{i:0;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2391167296585800117";}i:1;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEvIfy_hxm1";}i:2;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599269376;}i:3;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:1563:"I definitely have landforms on my brain this week 🏝🏔⁣
⁣
I recently put some landform work on our geography shelves to begin teaching the 10 basic landforms: cape, bay, lake, island, peninsula, gulf, strait, isthmus, system of lakes, and archipelago. (I just saved some of our shelf work to my “Geography” stories highlight, if you want to check it out.)⁣
⁣
I discovered this work at the beginning of the shut down in March, and my 5.5yo and I had a great time exploring all of the forms, and he had clearly mastered this work.⁣
⁣
Now I look forward to introducing my 3.5yo to this work, and to expanding my 5.5yo’s knowledge of other landforms (using the stunning unit study work from @stephhathawaydesigns)⁣
⁣
In the meantime, I thought today was the perfect moment to #flashbackfriday some of the work my 5yo and I did back in the spring to learn about landforms.⁣
⁣
The first three pictures are from spring and feature three variations: cheese (my personal favorite 😂🧀), @lego and baking soda! The fourth photo is of a landform work I just put on our shelf this evening, inspired by @mamashappyhive.⁣
⁣
Enjoy and get creative!⁣
